sample.Persons

Class JuridicalPerson

  • java.lang.Object
    • sample.Persons.JuridicalPerson
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class JuridicalPerson
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    It is a class which represents a user - juridical person.
    It contains some basic information like Title, BirthYear, Location, OSREOUCode.
    It also has all essential information about the user, on which all the taxes are based, and its Taxes.
    And as it's an application, the class contains also user's login and password for access control.
    See Also:

      • JuridicalPerson

        public JuridicalPerson(java.lang.String login,
                       java.lang.String password,
                       java.lang.String title,
                       int birthYear,
                       java.lang.String location,
                       int osreouCode)
        Constructor which determines a common information about the user of juridical type.
        Parameters:
        login - is a one of two fields which are used while authorisation in the application (login).
        password - is a one of two fields which are used while authorisation in the application (password).
        title - is a field which keeps the title (Title).
        birthYear - is a field which keeps a year of initiation (BirthYear).
        location - is a field which keeps a contry where it is placed (Location).
        osreouCode - is a field which keeps a number of the user in state register (OSREOUCode).

      • SetAdditionalInf

        public void SetAdditionalInf(double income,
                             double primeCost,
                             boolean excise,
                             boolean mineralUse,
                             double emissions,
                             double salaries,
                             double square,
                             boolean touristic,
                             int numberOfTourists,
                             double Percentageexcise)
        This method is made to fill the addition information, which is provided while running the application in userpage for calculating taxes. After saving all the data it also calls method CreateTaxes().
        Parameters:
        income - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: VAT, ExciseTax, IncomeTax, MineralResourcesTax, IncomeNatPerTax.
        primeCost - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: IncomeTax.
        excise - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: ExciseTax.
        mineralUse - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: MineralResourcesTax.
        emissions - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: EcologicalTax.
        salaries - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: SingleSocialContribution, MilitaryTax.
        square - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: RealtyTax, LandTax.
        touristic - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: TouristTax.
        numberOfTourists - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: TouristTax.
        Percentageexcise - is a field with essential information for such Taxes as: ExciseTax.

        JuridicalPerson, Tax
